text: In the spleens of mock-infected mice, there were no significant differences of IFN-γ levels between WT, IL-10 and TNF-α KO mice ( Figure S4A ). However, following JaOArS982 infection the levels of IFN-γ in TNF-α KO mice were significantly increased compared with those of WT mice at 5 and 9 days pi ( Figure S4B and C) . On the other hand, IL-2 and IL-4 levels in TNF-α KO mice were significantly higher than those of WT and IL-10 KO mice during mock infection ( Figure  S4A ) and following JaOArS982 infections ( Figure S4B to D) . Also, the level of IL-5 in TNF-α KO was decreased compared with WT and IL-10 KO mice at 5 days pi ( Figure S4B) .
